description.workDesk: A workdesk represents a unit of activity user performs in the process. It can be of different types based on the type of workdesk selected.
description.startEvent: Each process has an entry point that can be referred to as a Start Event. It consists of only outgoing links and no incoming links. It is added by default whenever a new process is created in the Process Tree.
description.task: Tasks allow users to define ad-hoc activities for a process and are invoked by Case type activities or workdesks in case of semi-structured or unstructured processes.
description.name: Displays task name in read-only mode.
description.description: Allows a user to specify a description of the task.
description.goal: Allows a user to set goal of the task.
description.instructions: Allows a user to specify instructions to complete the task.
description.repeatable: If this option is checked, the task can be used again and again by other users also. If unchecked, the task will be used only once.
description.notifyByEmail: Allows a user to send notification through an email.
description.turnaroundTime: Allows users to specify a TAT (Turnaround Time) by entering information in days, hours and minutes either using working days or calendar days.
description.dataExchange: This workstep is used to exchange data between iBPS and any third party database. Once the external DB server is registered and data source is selected, then tables/views/columns can be selected for fetching or updating data in other databases.
description.endEvent: The End Event workstep indicates the successful completion of a workitem in the process.
description.terminateEvent: Terminate Event is used to discard the workitems in a process by routing them to this workstep.
description.messageEnd: This worksteps transfers information onto a new process at the end of an existing process. Users can choose which data is to be mapped and exchanged between the two processes involved.
description.inclusiveDistribute: The Inclusive distribute workstep allows workitem to be created and distributed to collect workstep such that the users on those steps can process the item according to rule specified on distribute workstep.
description.inclusiveCollect: Corresponding to every Inclusive Distribute in the Process, there has to be an Inclusive Collect step to collect all the distributed instances back together and merge them back into a single instance for further routing in the process.
description.parallelDistribute: The Parallel Distribute workstep allows multiple workitems to be created and distributed to multiple worksteps such that the users on those steps can process the item simultaneously in parallel.
description.parallelCollect: Corresponding to every Parallel Distribute in the Process, a Collect step collects all the distributed instances back together and merges them back into a single instance for further routing in the process.
description.dataBasedExclusive: This step is used as an “OR” step in the process, from where the workitems will take alternate paths depending on their data and the Routing Criteria defined on this step. The definition of rules that govern the routing sequence of workitems is facilitated by this Data Based Exclusive Workstep.
description.eventWorkstep: Event workstep is used to re-initiate a process whenever it receives a message from any external source.
description.jmsProducer: JMS Producer workstep publishes a message containing XML to a particular JMS Destination. After publishing the XML, the workitem will move further in the process, while the External application will subscribe to that particular destination on the Application Server and will carry out the required operations in their system, as specified in the message XMLs.
description.jmsConsumer: The JMS Consumer workstep consumes the JMS messages published by external applications. MDBs (Message Driven Beans) will be deployed on an Application Server, which consumes the messages from the destination and carry out operations like Create, Save, Done & SaveAndDone on the workitems in the process.
description.timerEventWorkstep: The Timer workstep has been defined for the purpose of holding workitems for a specified time period. The workitems can be set on hold for a particular duration of time, in process, during which they will not be accessible to any user of the system for processing. After the expiration of the hold period the workitems are released back into the process.
description.conditionalStart: The Conditional Start event starts the process only after the condition defined in this workstep becomes true while executing the process.
description.robotWorkdesk: This workstep allows the user to integrate the process with Newgen’s new RPA (Robotic Process Automation) solution framework and automate tasks using recorded scripts.
description.receive: Receive Workstep is used to receive a request from external service in the form of a message.
description.reply: Reply workstep is used in conjunction with Receive workstep. It is used to send a response to a request previously accepted through an inbound message (receive) activity. These responses are only meaningful for request-response interactions.
description.email: Email Workstep is used to print, fax or email documents.
description.export: Export Workstep is used to export the workitem from process into the CSV file.
description.query: The Query workstep is a dangling workstep in a business process, which has no incoming or outgoing links. It serves the primary purpose of defining a view for the workitems when they are opened for the purpose of status tracking, from the Query WorkDesk.
description.webService: Webservice workstep enables any user to invoke an external webservice in the current workflow process. When the workitem lands on this workstep, the configured webservice will be invoked for all workitems either synchronously or asynchronously.
description.businessRule: The Business Rule workstep allows user to define business rule for the activities.
description.callActivity: Complex business processes can be broken into simpler processes and these simple processes can be linked together to form the main process. This feature allows the workitem to be automatically initiated for processing in a sub process, until which it remains suspended in the main process. After its completion in the sub-process, it resumes it processing in the parent process.
description.sapAdapter: The functions registered in SAP Tab of Catalog Definition can be used in this SAP Adapter Workstep.
description.dmsAdapter: The DMS Adapter workstep allows the user to archive the workitem data and document in the underlying Document management System.
description.caseWorkdesk: This workstep allows the process designer to associate tasks with the step so that when the process comes to this step, the associated tasks can be performed by the user
description.dataObject: Data Object is used to store the information related to the object’s documents etc. It does not have an impact on process execution.
description.textAnnotation: Text annotation is one of the standard artifacts in BPMN 2.0. It is used to write extra information and explanations about elements in a process, but it does not affect its execution.
description.groupBox: Group Box is used to define set of activities for same individual user/group of users and activities within it are executed at the same time.
description.timerStart: This event specifies the wait time required (along with any other scheduling conditions) before initiating a Work Item. Cyclic time to initiate the work-item, e.g. every month, week, day etc. can also be configured through its settings.
description.omsAdapter: OMS Adaptor enables process designer to connect with Newgen’s CCM (Customer Communication Management) suite for generating on-demand personalized communication and deliver consistent communications across multiple channels.
description.messageStart: This WorkStep is able to receive an incoming message by exposing a Webservice, through which message variables are also received. A condition can be defined on the basis of message variables received. A new WorkItem is created only if the initiation condition(s) are met.
